g.text: In UI layer you can ﬁnd all code / logic related to any used
framework like Next.js or React.js. Here you can ﬁnd any use
of cli tools, conﬁgurations, HTML markup, styles etc.
Generally everything what is not related to data fetching or
business logic. You can ﬁnd here also setup for navigation or
themes used within the app. Any tests related setup can be
Data store is a layer which contains of store and data which is
stored there. It's also visible via presenter so you can access
it either on presentation layer or on ui layer if for example
you would like to just perform operations on store without
any action on data source. There are few variants of
approach to Data store layer isolation here but this one is
probably most convenient for most developers as it's a 'in the
Presentation layer access is deﬁned within abstraction of
presenter. It contains whole framework of communication
and potential output deﬁnition. You can communicate with
presentation via Request Objects. If you need data from data
source you need to ask presenter for it. Presenter returns
presentation model which you can use on markup.
Sometimes for special cases you may use mapper if you need
for a speciﬁc screen updated deﬁnition of that model
Data store access logic is a gateway for any
data, it contains all of the logic required to get
data and potentially map it. It's also a form of
isolation between any markup related logic and
strictly logic related to data based operations
Markup logic contains classic logic related to
handling user actions performed on markup,
like handling clicks, lifecycle of components,
